Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addPinToPinGroup(25.10)                                addPinToPinGroup(25.10)

Name
       addPinToPinGroup  -  Adds a module port to specified pin group that was
       created by createPinGroup command

Syntax
         addPinToPinGroup

       [-help]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       -pinGroup <pinGroupName>

       -pin {<pinName> | <pinNameList>}

       Adds a module port to specified pin group  that  was  created  by  cre-
       atePinGroup  command.  You  can  use  this command after defining a net
       group.

       Note: You can use this command for the top-level also.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the name of a module. This parameter is  not  required
              for top-level ports.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each addPinToPinGroup parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man addPinToPinGroup

       -pinGroup <pinGroupName>
              Specifies the name of the created pin group.

              Data_type: string, required

       -pin {<pinName> | <pinNameList>}
              Specifies the name of a module port. You can  specify  wildcards
              (*?) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              * The  following command adds the module SH17's port RASN to pin
                group pin17:

                addPinToPinGroup -cell SH17 -pinGroup pin17 -pin RASN

              * The following command adds the top-level  port  ADDER  to  pin
                group PIN_GRP_TOP

                addPinToPinGroup -pinGroup PIN_GRP_TOP -pin ADDER

